  "original_title": "\u0d9a\u0db3\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dbb \u0d9a\u0ddc\u0da7\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dc0 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dd0\u0dad\u0dd2\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The report about the mountain tiger to the minister",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The final report of the three-member committee appointed to investigate the death of the mountain tiger that died on August 7 due to being caught in a trap at Summerhill Estate has been handed over to the Minister of Agriculture, Wildlife and Forest Resources Conservation Mr. Mahinda Amaraweera.",
        "This report was handed over to the minister by the secretary of the ministry, Mrs. Chandra Herath, and the additional secretary H. D. Ratnayake, Taraka Prasad Director (Health Management), Director Operations (National Zoo Department) H. that. Mr. Anoma Priyadarshini participated in this event.",
        "The committee that investigated the death of the mountain tiger has made 25 recommendations regarding the protection of the mountain tiger population in this report.",
        "Also, in this Summerhill incident, the investigation revealed that the tiger had died due to the damage to its internal organs due to being caught in a trap made of wire and hanging from a tall tree for hours, and that the animal had not fallen under the tree."
      ],
